Trevor Noah attends the 50th NAACP Image Awards at Dolby Theatre on March 30, 2019 in Hollywood, California. JOHANNESBURG - South African comedian Trevor Noah has been nominated for a Critics Choice award for his Netflix special Trevor Noah: Son of Patricia. The Daily Show host, who is nominated in the Best Comedy Special category, said the nomination was an honour. READ: Trevor Noah nominated for Grammy "What a way to start off the week! Thank you @criticschoice for this incredible honour", said Noah. The awards ceremony will take place on Sunday, 12 January 2020. It has been an incredible year for Noah, after he also managed to bag a Grammy nomination for his comedy special. What a way to start off the week! Thank you @criticschoice for this incredible honour. 🙏🏾 A post shared by  Trevor Noah (@trevornoah) on Dec 9, 2019 at 10:38am PST